<TITLE> Noor Hossain remembered </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 10 (bdnews24.com)--President Zillur Rahman has said Noor Hossain's sacrifice has helped restore democracy in the country. The president made the statement in his message marking Shaheed Noor Hossain Day on Tuesday. Noor Hossain, a leader of Awami League's youth wing Jatiya Jubo League, was killed in police firing on this day in 1987 in an anti-autocracy demonstration during the regime of H M Ershad, with the slogan 'Down with autocracy, let democracy be freed' inscribed in white paint on his chest and back. The Ershad government fell in 1990 and democracy restored. Many parties and organisations are observing the day with various programmes to mark the day. Paying homage to Noor Hossain, the president in his message said: "This valiant fighter, who was at the front of the procession, had given blood to build a non-communal, progressive and democratic Bangladesh." "Following his sacrifice democracy was restored in 1990," he said. Terming Nov 10 as a memorable day, prime minister Sheikh Hasina said in her message: "The sacrifice of Jubo League leader Shaheed Noor Hossain geared up the movement of pro-democratic people against the then autocratic ruler." "The aim of the government is to form a Bangladesh free of suppression and deprivation," she said. She paid deep respect to the memories of all martyrs including Shaheed Noor Hossain who sacrificed their lives in the struggle of democracy. Programmes Ruling Awami League, Jubo League, Chhatra League, Bangabandhu Sanskritik Jote and Shaheed Noor Hossain Sangsad have taken up various programmes to mark the day. The programmes include placing wreathes at the grave of Noor Hosain at Jurain, paying tributes at Shaheed Noor Hossain Square, discussion sessions and offering milad and doa mahfil. bdn
